MAP - Enum constant in enum class net.pinger.disguise.item.XMaterial
Adding this to the duplicated list will give you a filled map for 1.13+ versions and removing it from duplicated list will still give you a filled map in -1.12 versions.
matchDefinedXMaterial(String, byte) - Static method in enum class net.pinger.disguise.item.XMaterial
The main method that parses the given material name and data value as an XMaterial.
matchXMaterial(int, byte) - Static method in enum class net.pinger.disguise.item.XMaterial
Deprecated.
this method loops through all the available materials and matches their ID using XMaterial.getId() which takes a really long time. Plugins should no longer support IDs. If you want, you can make a Map cache yourself. This method obviously doesn't work for 1.13+ and will not be supported. This is only here for debugging purposes.
matchXMaterial(String) - Static method in enum class net.pinger.disguise.item.XMaterial
Parses the given material name as an XMaterial with a given data value in the string if attached.
matchXMaterial(ItemStack) - Static method in enum class net.pinger.disguise.item.XMaterial
Parses the given item as an XMaterial using its material and data value (durability) if not a damageable item ItemStack.getDurability().
matchXMaterial(Material) - Static method in enum class net.pinger.disguise.item.XMaterial
Parses the given material as an XMaterial.
